    "content": "<p>Which of the following pairs form the same osazone?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": " Glucose and fructose\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": " Glucose and galactose\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": " Glucose and arabinose\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": " Lactose and maltose"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>During osazone formation (when sugars are reacted with phenylhydrazine) the reaction occurs at $C_1$ and $C_2$ while rest of the position remains intact. Since glucose and fructose differ from each other only in the arrangement of atom at $C_1$ and $C_2$, therefore they give the same osazone.</p>",
